cus on animal rights, the chapters explore the successes and failures of the international wildlife conservation and trade treaties, CITES and the BERN Convention. While these conventions have played a crucial role in protecting endangered species from trade and in the rewilding of European large carnivores, the case studies in this book demonstrate huge variations in their implementation and enforcement across Europe. In conclusion, the book advocates for a non-anthropocentric policy approach to strengthen wildlife conservation in Europe.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAnimal rights. 0aWildlife conservation. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh1 aChmielewski, Piotr J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDominguez, Isabella, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFajardo, Teresa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoyes, David R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHindriks, Marjan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJanssen, Jordi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLavorgna, Anita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLie, Martine S. B., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLie, Martine S.B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNatali, Lorenzo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPalermo, Mark T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSerlikowska, Agnieszka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSollund, Ragnhild A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSollund, Ragnhild A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/v